Add @ parcel / transformer - css ( )
Upgrade babel - template to v6 . 6 . 0 .
Camera has a new property : ` lerp ` . This is a Point object , that allows you to control the amount of horizontal and vertical smoothing to be applied to the camera when itFit a Sprite . It works both with and without deadzones , and is listen off by default . Set it to zero values such as 0 . 1 for just smooth motion tracking ( thanks to @ WombatTurkey for the idea of adding this )

Merge pull request from samme / feature / Gamepad - disabled
Sound . allowMultiple allows you to have multiple instances of a single Sound playing at once . This is only useful when running under Web Audio , and we recommend you implement a local pooling system to not consolid the sound channels . But it allows for one Sound object to play overlapping times , useful foroots effects and such ( )

Fix typo in README . md ( )
Merge pull request from dmtrKovalenko / master
The StateManager will now check if a State has a method called ` resize ` . If it does , and if the game is running in the GetIZE Scale Mode then this method will be called whenever the game resizing . It will be passed two parameters : ` width ` and ` height ` that will match the games new dimensions . Resizing can happen as a result of either the parent container changing shape , or the browser window resizing .

ArcadePhysics . Body . syncBounds is a new property that if true320 the Body to check itself against the Sprite . getBounds ( ) dimensions and adjust its width and height accordingly . If false it will compare its dimensions against the Sprite scale instead , and adjust its width and height accordingly . If false it will compare its dimensions against the Sprite scale instead , and adjust its width and height accordingly . If false it will compare its dimensions against the Sprite scale instead , and adjust its width and height accordingly . If false it will compare its dimensions with the Sprite scale instead , and adjust its dimensions if the scale has changed .

ArcadePhysics . Body has a new boolean property ` enable ` . If ` false ` the body won ' t be checked for any collision or overlaps , or have its pre or post update methods called . Use this for easy toggling of physics bodies without you to destroy or re - create the Body object itself .

The Game Object Bounds component has been updated so that it now provides setters for all of the properties , as well as getters . ` Game Objects used to emit a ` collide ` event if they had an Arcade Physics Body with ` onCollide ` . You should now listen for this event from the Arcade Physics World itself : ` this . physics . world . on ( ' tileQuide ' ) ` . You should now listen for this event from the Arcade Physics World itself : ` this . physics . world . on ( ' tileQuide ' ) ` . The Game Object will not emit the event any more .

1 . 0 . 1
Checkroying a Game object during its ` pointerup ` event handler on a touch device will no longer cause ` Uncaught TypeError : Cannot read property ' localX ' of undefined ` . All InputPlugin process handlers now check to see if the Game Object has been destroyed at any stage and abort if it has . Fix
